GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
H 1
HOUSE BILL 337
Short Title: City of Southport/Deannexations. (Local)
Sponsors: Representative Miller.
For a complete list of sponsors, refer to the North Carolina General Assembly web site.
Referred to: State and Local Government, if favorable, Finance, if favorable, Rules, Calendar,
and Operations of the House
March 10, 2025
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT REMOVING CERTAIN DESCRIBED PROPERTY FROM THE CORPORATE
3 LIMITS OF THE CITY OF SOUTHPORT.
4 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
5 SECTION 1. The following described property, identified by Brunswick County
6 Tax Office Parcel Identification Number, is removed from the corporate limits of the City of
7 Southport:
8 221MB015, 221MB020, and 221MB02001.
9 SECTION 2. This act has no effect upon the validity of any liens of the City of
10 Southport for ad valorem taxes or special assessments outstanding before the effective date of
11 this act. Such liens may be collected or foreclosed upon after the effective date of this act as
12 though the property were still within the corporate limits of the City of Southport.
13 SECTION 3. This act becomes effective June 30, 2025. Property in the territory
14 described in Section 1 of this act as of January 1, 2025, is no longer subject to municipal taxes
15 for taxes imposed for taxable years beginning on or after July 1, 2025.
*H337-v-1*

